<br>
 AA that reduces resists was mentioned by the original poster. Regardless of dmg type sure; that would be about 12 AA's for an across the board resist mod................... if we can get it, fine. AA that gives us a finishing blow we already have, manaburn. <br>
<br>
improved fast casting we already have, for both nukes and beneficial spells. <br>
<br>
I just don't want another expansion where we have exactly the same types of AA's we've always had, that's boring. Sure, higher crit% is nice, but i really don't even notice that much of a difference between my maxed crits now, and my maxed Luclin crits.  If we get AA's that give us increased dmg focus for fire, magic, and cold, while lowering resists with each magic type, it would be different from all AA's before it, also giving wizards, as masters of DD, a great way to separate themselves from mages, necros, and druids. <br>
<br>
