Ok, I guess you don't know what nerf means. If rogues are suddenly upgraded, they may take over as the biggest damage, but that doesn't change the amount of damage wizard does. So yes, wizards are STILL going to be as powerful as they where before rogues got upgraded, just not as powerful as rogues. That, by definition IS NOT A NERF. It's an upgrade for rogues.<br>
<br>
If something DOES NOT GET CHANGED, THEN IT CAN'T BE A FUCKING NERF. How hard is that to understand? For something to be nerfed it necessarily has to be changed to the detriment of the player.<br>
<br>
Relative power and nerfs are mutually exclusive, one does not depend on the other. I know power is relative, I am not refusing to understand that. You are simply refusing to understand that one mans upgrade does not equal another mans nerfs.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah Qaman, I would have to disagree. You can outpace SoS with Ice spells (all figures unfocused) -<br>
<br>
Tears of Marr + Ice Spear of Solist + Draught of E'ci = 4190 damage in 18.75 seconds for 223 DPS. You can chain these 3 spells with little fear of agro from the time you engage the mob. (Damage figure takes into account 20% resist rate with ToM)<br>
<br>
Strike of Solusek + Concussion = 2740 damage in 14.5 seconds for 189 DPS. You can skip a concussion here and there, but the max DPS attainable 267 if you never cast concussion and chain SoS, but you know you would be summoned and splattered rather quickly.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wandork>Wandor K</A> at: 6/11/03 4:48 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etelka>Etelka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 589<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 4:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard of Fire, Ice or Magic ?</span><hr size=1> Leaving this discussion. This is pointless. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.wxs.nl/~tom.van.der.veen/Sig-custom.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 3523<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 6:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wizard of Fire, Ice or Magic ?</span><hr size=1> &gt;Strike of Solusek + Concussion = 2740 damage in 14.5 seconds for 189 DPS. You can skip a concussion here and there, but the max DPS attainable 267 if you never cast concussion and chain SoS, but you know you would be summoned and splattered rather quickly. <br>
